Note:
Runa Core Plugin Shared Module

Provides shared types, error classes, concurrency primitives, and utility functions for the Runa plugin system. All plugin modules must import from this module to ensure consistency, robustness, and production-readiness.
:End Note

Note: Error Types
Type PluginError is Error
Type PluginDiscoveryError is PluginError
Type PluginRegistrationError is PluginError
Type DependencyResolutionError is PluginError
Type PluginNotFoundError is PluginError
Type ServiceRegistrationError is PluginError
Type PluginGenerationError is PluginError
Type PluginSecurityError is PluginError

Note: Concurrency Primitives
Type Lock is Dictionary with:
    acquire as Function returns None
    release as Function returns None
    try_acquire as Function returns Boolean
    is_locked as Function returns Boolean

Process called "create_lock" returns Lock:
    Let locked be false
    Return Lock with:
        acquire as function():
            While locked:
                sleep(0.001)
            Set locked to true
        release as function():
            Set locked to false
        try_acquire as function():
            If not locked:
                Set locked to true
                Return true
            Return false
        is_locked as function():
            Return locked

Type RWLock is Dictionary with:
    acquire_read as Function returns None
    acquire_write as Function returns None
    release_read as Function returns None
    release_write as Function returns None

Process called "create_rwlock" returns RWLock:
    Let readers be 0
    Let writer be false
    Return RWLock with:
        acquire_read as function():
            While writer:
                sleep(0.001)
            Set readers to readers + 1
        release_read as function():
            Set readers to readers - 1
        acquire_write as function():
            While writer or readers > 0:
                sleep(0.001)
            Set writer to true
        release_write as function():
            Set writer to false

Note: Utility Functions
Process called "list_plugin_files" that takes path as String returns List[String]:
    Let plugin_files be list containing
    Let entries be file.list_directory(path)
    For each entry in entries:
        Let full_path be path plus "/" plus entry
        If file.is_directory(full_path):
            Let manifest_path be full_path plus "/plugin.toml"
            If file.exists(manifest_path):
                Add full_path to plugin_files
        Otherwise if entry ends with ".runa-plugin":
            Add full_path to plugin_files
    Return plugin_files

Process called "is_valid_semver" that takes version as String returns Boolean:
    Let pattern be regex.compile("^(\\d+)\\.(\\d+)\\.(\\d+)(-[\\w\\.]+)?(\\+[\\w\\.]+)?$")
    Return regex.matches(pattern, version)

Process called "is_compatible_runa_version" that takes required_versions as List[String] returns Boolean:
    Let current_version be get_runa_version()
    For each requirement in required_versions:
        If satisfies_version_requirement(current_version, requirement):
            Return true
    Return false

Process called "satisfies_version_requirement" that takes version as String and requirement as String returns Boolean:
    If requirement starts with "^":
        Return satisfies_caret_requirement(version, requirement[1:])
    Otherwise if requirement starts with "~":
        Return satisfies_tilde_requirement(version, requirement[1:])
    Otherwise if requirement contains "-":
        Let parts be split(requirement, "-")
        Return version_in_range(version, parts[0], parts[1])
    Otherwise:
        Return version equals requirement

Process called "read_toml" that takes path as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let content be file.read(path)
    Return toml.parse(content)

Process called "map_toml_to_manifest" that takes data as Dictionary[String, Any] returns PluginManifest:
    Note: Map TOML data to PluginManifest structure
    Return PluginManifest with:
        plugin as data["plugin"]
        compatibility as data["compatibility"]
        dependencies as data["dependencies"]
        capabilities as data["capabilities"]
        configuration as data["configuration"]
        build as data["build"]

Process called "generate_uuid" returns String:
    Return crypto.uuid4()

Process called "validate_service_interface" that takes interface as Any returns Boolean:
    Note: Validate that the service interface meets required contract
    If not hasattr(interface, "execute"):
        Return false
    If not callable(interface.execute):
        Return false
    Return true

Process called "get_runa_version" returns String:
    Return "1.0.0"  Note: Replace with dynamic version lookup in production

Process called "sleep" that takes seconds as Float returns None:
    Note: Platform-agnostic sleep
    Import time
    time.sleep(seconds) 

Note: Additional Core Types
Type Module is Dictionary with:
    main as Function
    initialize as Optional[Function]
    start as Optional[Function]
    stop as Optional[Function]
    reload as Optional[Function]
    cleanup as Optional[Function]
    path as String
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type FileWatcher is Dictionary with:
    on_change as Function that takes handler as Function returns None
    stop as Function returns None
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type TestResults is Dictionary with:
    passed as Integer
    failed as Integer
    errors as List[String]
    details as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type CoverageReport is Dictionary with:
    coverage_percent as Float
    files as Dictionary[String, Float]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Note: Additional Utility Functions
Process called "file_exists" that takes path as String returns Boolean:
    Return file.exists(path)

Process called "parse_toml_file" that takes path as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let content be file.read(path)
    Return toml.parse(content)

Process called "validate_plugin_manifest" that takes manifest as Dictionary[String, Any] returns ValidationResult:
    Let errors be list containing
    If "plugin" not in manifest:
        Add "Missing [plugin] section" to errors
    If "id" not in manifest["plugin"]:
        Add "Missing plugin id" to errors
    If not is_valid_semver(manifest["plugin"]["version"]):
        Add "Invalid semantic version format" to errors
    If "compatibility" not in manifest:
        Add "Missing [compatibility] section" to errors
    If not is_compatible_runa_version(manifest["compatibility"]["runa_version"]):
        Add "Incompatible Runa version requirement" to errors
    Return ValidationResult with:
        is_valid as (length of errors is equal to 0)
        errors as errors

Process called "is_compatible_version" that takes required as String and current as String returns Boolean:
    If required starts with "^":
        Return satisfies_caret_requirement(required[1:], current)
    Otherwise if required starts with "~":
        Return satisfies_tilde_requirement(required[1:], current)
    Otherwise:
        Return required equals current

Process called "current_runa_version" returns String:
    Return get_runa_version()

Process called "load_module_from_file" that takes path as String returns Module:
    Note: Platform-specific dynamic module loading
    Return system.load_module(path)

Process called "create_plugin_context" that takes manifest as Dictionary[String, Any] returns PluginContext:
    Return PluginContext with:
        config as manifest.get("config", dictionary containing)
        state as dictionary containing
        communication as create_plugin_communication()
        api as create_plugin_api()
        sandbox as create_sandbox_context(manifest)

Process called "unload_plugin_module" that takes plugin_id as String returns None:
    system.unload_module(plugin_id)
    Return None

Process called "get_plugin_path" that takes plugin_id as String returns String:
    Return system.get_plugin_directory(plugin_id)

Process called "find_test_files" that takes path as String returns List[String]:
    Return file.find_files(path, pattern as "*_test.runa")

Process called "execute_tests" that takes files as List[String] returns TestResults:
    Return system.run_tests(files)

Process called "current_timestamp" returns Float:
    Return system.current_time_millis()

Process called "create_plugin_communication" returns PluginCommunication:
    Return PluginCommunication with:
        send_message as function(message): None
        receive_message as function(handler): None
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "create_plugin_api" returns PluginAPI:
    Return PluginAPI with:
        ui as dictionary containing
        editor as dictionary containing
        workspace as dictionary containing
        language as dictionary containing
        debug as dictionary containing
        testing as dictionary containing
        scm as dictionary containing
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "create_sandbox_context" that takes manifest as Dictionary[String, Any] returns SandboxContext:
    Return SandboxContext with:
        permissions as manifest.get("permissions", list containing)
        resource_limits as manifest.get("resources", dictionary containing)
        metadata as manifest.get("metadata", dictionary containing) 